title: Toshiko Akiyoshi: on being a Japanese jazz artist
description:
Interview with Toshiko Akiyoshi by Fred Bouchard as a part of the Berklee Oral History Project.  Recorded September 29, 2007.

The Berklee Oral History Project is a Stan Getz Library-supported initiative to chronicle the rich and diverse history of Berklee and Boston music from those who have lived, shaped and defined it. Join liberal arts faculty and journalist Fred Bouchard as he interviews some of the greats: http://library.berklee.edu/archives
creator: The Jazz Jousters & Es-K
